1
00:00:01,760 --> 00:00:08,780
If I go to Solution Explorer and open the Program.cs file, you can see in the routing we have something

2
00:00:08,780 --> 00:00:11,060
called as controller and action.

3
00:00:11,660 --> 00:00:14,090
Remember these keywords for now.

4
00:00:14,780 --> 00:00:21,410
If you open the Solution Explorer again, you will notice we have a folder with the name of controllers.

5
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:24,350
We have models and we have views.

6
00:00:25,050 --> 00:00:28,440
That basically defines the MVC keyword.

7
00:00:28,950 --> 00:00:33,030
MVC stands for models, Views and Controllers.

8
00:00:33,270 --> 00:00:36,480
But how do all three of them come together?

9
00:00:36,930 --> 00:00:40,200
Let me show you a brief overview about that.

10
00:00:40,710 --> 00:00:46,320
In the MVC architecture, as I said, first letter stands for model.

11
00:00:46,530 --> 00:00:49,980
Model represents the shape of the data.

12
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:54,160
So if you have any tables or if you have any classes.

13
00:00:54,180 --> 00:00:56,490
Model will have all of that.

14
00:00:57,170 --> 00:01:03,050
And what I mean by class is let's say you are building an e-commerce application where you have products,

15
00:01:03,050 --> 00:01:08,690
you will have orders, you will have order details, shopping cart and much more.

16
00:01:08,990 --> 00:01:12,860
Models will basically have all of those class files.

17
00:01:13,890 --> 00:01:19,320
Next we have something called As View, which stands for the user interface.

18
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:26,500
So whatever you see on the screen, that is the view part of the MVC application.

19
00:01:26,770 --> 00:01:29,260
So model represents the data.

20
00:01:29,260 --> 00:01:32,860
And what you see on the screen is the user interface.

21
00:01:32,890 --> 00:01:40,780
Like if you have a form or if you have a fancy chart that you see on the browser, all of that is represented

22
00:01:40,780 --> 00:01:41,800
by The View.

23
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:46,970
View will control the HTML element of your web project.

24
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:53,000
Now you have the view where you have the fancy HTML that you see on the screen.

25
00:01:53,330 --> 00:02:00,740
But when you have the data, you will have to process or even fetch that data because data might be

26
00:02:00,740 --> 00:02:02,030
inside a database.

27
00:02:02,180 --> 00:02:09,380
So you need something to fetch that data and display that in a table on your HTML view that you have.

28
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:17,540
That missing piece or heart of the MVC application is the controller, which is the last piece of the

29
00:02:17,540 --> 00:02:18,920
missing block here.

30
00:02:19,610 --> 00:02:27,500
Controller will basically handle the user request and it will act as an interface between model and

31
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,070
view.

32
00:02:28,490 --> 00:02:35,900
What happens is when a user clicks on one of the button or opens the website, the request will first

33
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,370
go to the controller.

34
00:02:37,730 --> 00:02:42,180
Controller will then determine what model it has to fetch.

35
00:02:42,210 --> 00:02:49,620
It will retrieve all the data that is needed using the models and then it will pass all the data that

36
00:02:49,620 --> 00:02:53,160
is required to be displayed to the view component.

37
00:02:53,610 --> 00:03:00,900
What view will do is it will add all the data in its HTML formatting and pass that data back to the

38
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:09,000
controller and then controller will send that response back and the data or website will be displayed

39
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,440
on your screen.

40
00:03:10,770 --> 00:03:18,360
So one thing that you should always remember is in an MVC architecture controller is heart of your application.

41
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:25,420
And it might sound like I'm repeating this over and over again, but MVC architecture can be tricky

42
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:28,240
to understand if you are getting started.

43
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:30,550
So let's walk through that again.

44
00:03:30,670 --> 00:03:35,080
When a user opens a website, it goes to a controller.

45
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:42,590
Controller will then fetch data from the models or wherever it has to do process that data.

46
00:03:42,610 --> 00:03:46,460
Like there might be some conversion or anything that it has to do.

47
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:53,710
And once the data is in good shape, it will pass that data to the view on that static HTML.

48
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:57,310
It will add the data that controller has passed.

49
00:03:57,550 --> 00:04:03,910
Like in View, we might have defined that there is a table, but what data that table needs, we will

50
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:06,220
pass that from controller to the View.

51
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:10,960
Then Vue will add that data in the HTML and final content.

52
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:18,339
It will return back to the controller, which will ultimately be passed on to the user screen and user

53
00:04:18,339 --> 00:04:20,600
can see the complete website.

54
00:04:21,230 --> 00:04:27,020
This, my friends, is the basic architecture of an MVC application.

55
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:35,140
Our controller can have many action method action method basically define the endpoints in a controller

56
00:04:35,140 --> 00:04:38,430
and we will uncover that in the next video.

57
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:42,160
But there is something called as action methods there as well.

58
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:47,620
If I go back to the website here, you can see where we have the default route.

59
00:04:47,650 --> 00:04:54,220
We are saying that if nothing is defined, you should go to the home controller and there you have index

60
00:04:54,220 --> 00:04:56,560
action and something called as ID.

61
00:04:57,610 --> 00:05:00,220
Let's ignore that right now.

62
00:05:00,220 --> 00:05:06,970
You know the basic MVC architecture and let's cover this routing in the next video.

